I think the crux of the issue here is that Flutter's floating label slightly extends above the height of the outline TextField.  This is probably wrong...  I think it should probably be included in the total height of the TextField.

### Solution

Update the math that calculates the height of the field to include the part of `label` that extends above the field.

https://github.com/flutter/flutter/blob/327fde3e65a6fe3454c9788418915dcd2adf3e8c/packages/flutter/lib/src/material/input_decorator.dart#L1091

This will probably break many visual diff tests.  Any that include an outlined TextField with a label would be affected, even if they are not floating in the image. Maybe this can be done as a part of https://github.com/flutter/flutter/pull/121753, which will also break a lot of related tests.

### Workaround

Just add a little bit of space above affected TextFields.

